4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT GENERALLY REVISING LAWS RELATED TO THE
5 DETERMINATION OF THE BEST INTERESTS OF THE CHILD IN CUSTODY AND ADOPTION
6 PROCEEDINGS; AMENDING SECTIONS 40-4-212 AND 42-5-107, MCA; AND PROVIDING AN EFFECTIVE
7 DATE.”
8
9 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
10
11 Section 1. Section 40-4-212, MCA, is amended to read:
12 "40-4-212. Best interest of child. (1) The court shall determine the parenting plan in accordance with
13 the best interest of the child. The court shall consider all relevant parenting factors, which may include but are
14 not limited to:
15 (a) the wishes of the child's parent or parents;
16 (b) the wishes of the child;
17 (c) the interaction and interrelationship of the child with the child's parent or parents and siblings
18 and with any other person who significantly affects the child's best interest;
19 (d) the child's adjustment to home, school, and community;
20 (e) the mental and physical health of all individuals involved;
21 (f) physical abuse or threat of physical abuse by one parent against the other parent or the child;
22 (g) chemical dependency, as defined in 53-24-103, or chemical abuse on the part of either parent;
23 (h) continuity and stability of care;
24 (i) developmental needs of the child;
25 (j) whether a parent has knowingly failed to pay birth-related costs that the parent is able to pay,
26 which is considered to be not in the child's best interests;
27 (k) whether a parent has knowingly failed to financially support a child that the parent is able to
28 support, which is considered to be not in the child's best interests;
